   <b>OBJECTIVE</b>

   </br>Nevo seeks to engage an independent QA analyst/team lead for a 3-4
   month project effort with possible part time follow on. This is a
   short-term fulltime contract situation.  Work will be done primarily
   at Nevo’s headquarters in Harvard Square, with occasional visits to
   the client site in southeast Massachusetts.

   </br>Nevo expects the QA analyst/team lead to define, direct, control,
   and directly contribute to testing activities for this multi tier
   Windows / .NET custom software development effort.</br>



   <b>MAJOR DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText"><li>Define quality goals, establish and lead a strategy and plan to achieve project quality goals

   </li><li>Assume full responsibility for the testing effort

   </li><li>Define specific testing deliverables and acceptance testing criteria

   </li><li>Propose appropriate and creative solutions to QA testing challenges

   </li><li>Develop test plans and execute tests

   </li><li>Guide one or more additional testers

   </li><li>Work collaboratively with developers to explain issues identified and to define acceptable resolution

   </li><li>Provide comprehensive test result reports

   </li><li>Develop testing schedules, estimates, budgets, and milestones

   </li><li>Define, implement, and complete testing activities within tight project deadlines

   </li><li>Recommend and manage QA tools appropriate for achieving quality goals

   </li><li>Partner with the project leader to communicate effectively with all stakeholders about the quality goals and status of the project

   </li><li>Work collaboratively with Nevo and client teams, driving a strong sense of constructive teamwork.
   </li></ul>

   <b>ESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText"><li>4+ years of professional QA experience, including some experience in professional services or consulting

   </li><li>2+ years experience leading QA test teams for Internet and desktop systems

   </li><li>Strong organizational skills, attention to detail; proven problem solving and team leadership skills; proven ability to learn quickly while applying knowledge effectively

   </li><li>Strong understanding of software development and quality assurance methodologies, especially rapid, iterative software development approaches

   </li><li>Comfortable in a multi-task, deadline-oriented environment

   </li><li>Excellent English written and verbal communication and interpersonal skills with an appreciation for and ability to communicate with and respond to the needs of diverse audiences.
   </li></ul>

   <b>DESIRABLE QUALIFICATIONS</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText"><li>Working knowledge of SQL and relational databases

   </li><li>Prior experience with scripting and running test sequences using automated testing tools
   </li></ul>

   <b>ADDITIONAL CONSIDERATIONS</b>

   <ul class="tightBodyText"><li>We expect this will be a 1099 contract position

   </li><li>Nevo will consider only direct applications by principals

   </li><li>No relocation benefits are available for this position
   </li></ul>

